Overview
------------------------------
Symantec ICSP App for Splunk gives quick overview of scan results from multiple ICSP devices.
* Author - Hideyuki Nishiura
* Version - 1.0
* Build - N/A
* Creates Index - False
* Prerequisites - This application is dependent on Status Indicator - Custom Visualization
* Compatible with:
   Splunk Enterprise version: 6.4 or higher
   Common Information Model: N/A
   OS: Platform independent

Prerequisite
------------------------------
* Symantec ICSP App for Splunk requires Visualizations Add-on below:
  Status Indicator - Custom Visualization
  https://splunkbase.splunk.com/app/3119/

Support
------------------------------
* Unsupported

Installation
------------------------------
* This App needs to be installed on Splunk Search Head in the case of Distributed environment.
* This App can be installed either through UI from "Manage Apps" or by extracting the compressed file into $SPLUNK_HOME$/etc/ap
ps folder.
* Restart Splunk after installation.

Setup
* This App uses two lookup files. You need edit or generate them.
   - host-location.csv
    This file stores hostname of ICSP device recorded in log file, name of the device(location name), and geo-location(latitude,longitude)
  - usb.ids.csv
    This file stores the list of USB devices information( VendorID,VendorName,ProductID,ProductName). You can add devices info, if your devices are not found in the list. Also, you can re-generate the file download from http://www.linux-usb.org/usb.ids, and run a search such like below:

source=“usb.ids" 
| rex field=_raw max_match=0 "[\r\n]\s+(?<ProductID>[\d\w]+)\s+(?<ProductName>[^\r\n]+)"
| rex field=_raw "^(?<VendorID>[\d\w]+)\s+(?<VendorName>[^\r\n]+)"
| eval Product=mvzip(ProductID,ProductName,":")
| fields - ProductID ProductName
| mvexpand Product
| rex field=Product "(?<ProductID>[^ ]+):(?<ProductName>.+)"
| table VendorID VendorName ProductID ProductName


